<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14937">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Moviemaking.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14955">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Discuss and demonstrate the proper elements of a good motion picture. In
      your discussion, include visual storytelling, rhythm, the 180-axis rule,
      camera movement, framing and composition of camera shots, and lens
      selection. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/BFwMRVwrKcA?si=uW4whxq0-SZjyFHJ" target="_blank"
        >Film Making Basics (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14938">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14938 mb-requirement-id-14950">
        (a) In a three- or four-paragraph treatment, tell the story you plan to
        produce, making sure that the treatment conveys a visual picture.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/puF9CkvmJt0?si=jiFW5a-I3X0vZDV4"
          target="_blank"
          >Film Production Explained, Each Step of the Production Process
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14938 mb-requirement-id-14951">
        (b) Prepare a storyboard for your motion picture. <br /><br /><b
          >Note: </b
        >This can be done with rough sketches and stick figures. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/yPtqHdQcOOw?si=24Rdiz36nJTayneu"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is a Storyboard and Why Is It Important? Pre-Production
          Filmmaking (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14938 mb-requirement-id-14939">
        (c) Demonstrate the following motion picture shooting techniques:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14939 mb-requirement-id-14940">
        (1) Using a tripod <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pAvn034VcCg" target="_blank"
          >7 Tripod Tricks for Filmaking (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14939 mb-requirement-id-14941">
        (2) Panning a camera <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Km7Rfpda_Lw" target="_blank"
          >Camera Panning (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14939 mb-requirement-id-14942">
        (3) Framing a shot <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5UE3jz_O_EM" target="_blank"
          >Reverse Shot (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/DAwz2Wnrr90?feature=share"
          target="_blank"
          >Frame it Right Essential Framing (short video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14939 mb-requirement-id-14943">
        (4) Selecting an angle <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/nfHvSnILXl0?si=9ObCi1MwUvu3CHyW"
          target="_blank"
          >Film making 101: 5 Camera Angles (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/SlNviMsi0K0" target="_blank"
          >12 CAMERA ANGLES to Enhance Your Films (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14939 mb-requirement-id-14944">
        (5) Selecting proper lighting <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/r2nD_knsNrc" target="_blank"
          >Ultimate Guide to Cinematic Lighting (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/zdZ2zza5WbY?si=m3eF-8tZrS-NaOC5"
          target="_blank"
          >Zack Snyder Justice League Martian Man Hunter Meets Lois (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14939 mb-requirement-id-14945">
        (6) Handheld shooting <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/LuJdvwm8-0k" target="_blank"
          >5 Tips for Shooting Handheld Videos (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/PVmaJAmQ3yQ" target="_blank"
          >Birdman (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14938 mb-requirement-id-14946">
        (d) Using motion picture shooting techniques, plan ONE of the following
        programs. Start with a treatment and complete the requirement by
        presenting this program to a pack or your troop, patrol, or class.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14946 mb-requirement-id-14947">
        (1) Film a court of honor and show it to an audience. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/oPfet0ypjmY?si=flKBth5nUkcFZelI"
          target="_blank"
          >4 Videography Tips for Beginners (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14946 mb-requirement-id-14948">
        (2) Create a short feature of your own design, using the techniques you
        learned. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/kZWH6OBDdR0?si=e1VBvG2lGwQHKqEY"
          target="_blank"
          >10 Tips for Beginner Videographers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14946 mb-requirement-id-14949">
        (3) Shoot a vignette that could be used to train a new Scout in a
        Scouting skill. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/cLLuuV_57JY?si=vcdpLOuyRcHeC1jf"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Make a Great Instructional Video (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14952">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14952 mb-requirement-id-14953">
        (a) With your parent or guardian's permission and your counselor's
        approval, visit a film set or television production studio and watch how
        production work is done. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/zqUAiM-FLrs?si=xK2hkF_sD9zCzGcM"
          target="_blank"
          >Film Set Order of Operations (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14952 mb-requirement-id-14954">
        (b) Explain to your counselor the elements of the zoom lens and three
        important parts. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fRKsKR9wvqE" target="_blank"
          >How Lens Work in Camera (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/15h9iG-Rdwk?si=TUp4-HL00H50ZX79"
          target="_blank"
          >The Parts of a Camera Lens - Anatomy of a DSLR Lens (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14956">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14956 mb-requirement-id-14957">
        (a) Explore careers related to this merit badge. Research one career to
        learn about the training and education needed, costs, job prospects,
        salary, job duties, and career advancement. Your research methods may
        include—with your parent or guardian's permission—an internet or library
        search, an interview with a professional in the field, or a visit to a
        location where people in this career work. Discuss with your counselor
        both your findings and what about this profession might make it an
        interesting career. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CNMBMhNh2S0" target="_blank"
          >Top 10 Careers in Film &amp; Video Production (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14956 mb-requirement-id-14958">
        (b) Explore how you could use knowledge and skills from this merit badge
        to pursue a hobby or healthy lifestyle. Research any training needed,
        expenses, and organizations that promote or support it. Discuss with
        your counselor what short-term and long-term goals you might have if you
        pursued this. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/d30kfqueNKI" target="_blank"
          >Filmmaking as a Hobby - Getting Started (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
